OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776438666
OL,3,CStroud lido could reopen in time for
OL,4,Cthe school summer holidays
OL,6,FDozens of residents gathered outside
OL,7,Fthe council offices at Ebley Mill and
OL,8,Fchanted "only a fool would close the
OL,9,Fpool" ahead of the crunch strategy and
OL,10,Fresources committee which discussed
OL,11,Fthe lido.
OL,13,FMany proceeded to pack the public
OL,14,Fgallery and hear questions and answers
OL,15,Fon the issues affecting the pool and
OL,16,Fproposals for its future.
OL,18,FThe meeting heard how preliminary
OL,19,Ffindings from further investigations
OL,20,Fsuggest the foundation of the diving
OL,21,Fboard area is sound.
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@EO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776438666
OL,3,CStroud lido could reopen in time for
OL,4,Cthe school summer holidays
OL,6,FAnd council chiefs stressed they want
OL,7,Fto keep the lido open but it needs to
OL,8,Fbe made safe to do so and a long-term
OL,9,Fsolution will still be needed.
OL,11,FLabour group leader Katy Hofmann
OL,12,F(Rodborough) proposed an amendment
OL,13,Fwhich sought to explore ways to repair
OL,14,Fand open the lido in time for the
OL,15,Fsummer. This was seconded by committee
OL,16,Fchairman and Green Party council
OL,17,Fleader Chloe Turner (Minchinhampton).
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776438666
OL,3,CStroud lido could reopen in time for
OL,4,Cthe school summer holidays
OL,6,FCllr Hofmann said one of the main
OL,7,Freasons for bringing the amendment to
OL,8,Fthe original motion "didn't seem to
OL,9,Freflect the strong desire by the
OL,10,Fpublic and members of this committee
OL,11,Fto find a way to open the lido this
OL,12,Fsummer.
OL,14,F"I felt it didn't reflect a desire to
OL,15,Fact quickly to develop a plan to
OL,16,Fidentify costs for the repairs that
OL,17,Fare needed if the pool is to open this
OL,18,Fyear," she said.
OL,26,@pD@UOUvD@AOUzD@FO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776438666
OL,3,CStroud lido could reopen in time for
OL,4,Cthe school summer holidays
OL,6,FCllr Turner said she would very much
OL,7,Flike to support the proposals and
OL,8,Fsaid: "We've worked together to
OL,9,Fhopefully give us the mechanisms we
OL,10,Fneed to move as quickly as possible."
OL,12,FShe went on to say that officers have
OL,13,Fbeen working "absolutely flat out"
OL,14,Fbehind closed doors and she echoed
OL,15,FCllr Hofmann's comments.
OL,17,F"There is no question of people
OL,18,Fsitting on their hands here," she
OL,19,Fsaid. "We will go as fast as we
OL,20,Fpossibly can.
OL,26,@pD@GOUrD@eO]uD@NOUuD@bO]yD@AOUzD@]O]{D@
OL,26,AGOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
